parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt cable can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of a crash, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt cable comes loose
the seat belt sticks to the floor
the seat belt does not return to its normal position
the seat belt has a delayed return to its normal position
the seat belt has a sudden loss of pressure.

the cable drops out of the chamber
the shoulder belt anchorage becomes stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission bearings can cause the transmission to fail, leading to vehicle stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the transmission fluid hose can cause transmission failure, leading to vehicle stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.

symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.
